{"TopicId":132376,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Airstairs","CreatedByName":"JPmAn","CreatedById":121564,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-18T03:19:53Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JPmAn","CreatedById":121564,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-18T03:19:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about some airstairs to add on to the mk1 kabin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPmAn","CreatedById":121564,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-20T03:41:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnything? Your thoughts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tantalus","CreatedById":118982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-20T10:20:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure what you want to say with \u0022airstairs\u0022? Do you mean a crew hatch? So your kerbals can enter and leave the cabin from the side? This has been suggested i think \u00A0a dozen times. If you mean something different, you should give a bit more information.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and the mk1 cabin has crew hatches, but they are at the front and aft end, so mostly obstructed by other parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegards\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTantalus\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex","CreatedById":75164,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-20T18:29:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think they would really add anything meaningful. In my opinion, from what I\u0027ve looked up to learn what you mean, airstairs are very bulky additions to aircraft that wouldn\u0027t be very welcome in a spaceplane design. It\u0027s much simpler and lighter to use a \u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Telus-LV_Bay_Mobility_Enhancer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ETelus-LV Bay Mobility Enhancer\u003C/a\u003E, angled downwards, to provide a means of climbing up and onto a wing or directly to the hatch itself, which is my favorite method.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-20T19:48:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222420335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455963613\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118982\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tantalus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Tantalus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure what you want to say with \u0022airstairs\u0022? Do you mean a crew hatch? So your kerbals can enter and leave the cabin from the side? This has been suggested i think \u00A0a dozen times. If you mean something different, you should give a bit more information.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think when he says Air Stairs, he means Air Stairs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022?u=http%3A%2F%2Fimages.scribblelive.com%\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://images.duckduckgo.com/iu/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fimages.scribblelive.com%2F2011%2F12%2F6%2F25bb5124-e930-46b4-93ac-b264bf37102a_500.jpg\u0026amp;f=1\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure if they would be feasible with the way Kernels currently exit hatches.\u00A0 Plus it would really only work at KSC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Although, there are planes with built-in air stairs.\u00A0 This might be more feasible as the Kerbal could exit the plane inside a cutout once the stairs are deployed.\u00A0 However it would require new code from Squad.\u00A0 Specifically they would need a new module, something like \u0022DeployableHatch\u0022 that would prevent Kerbals from going EVA while an animation hasn\u0027t taken place yet.\u00A0 The mobility enhancers already sort of simulate this, but as we all know they do not work well with the new Mk1 Cockpit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Air_Force_One_June_12_2006.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3c/Air_Force_One_June_12_2006.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-20T19:59:08Z\u0022 title=\u002202/20/2016 07:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tantalus","CreatedById":118982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-21T20:08:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, these are called airstairs? Ok, seems i was on the wrong way then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Coga19000","CreatedById":125394,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-22T22:25:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110959\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110959-alshain/\u0022\u003E@Alshain\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Im ddefinetely not a grammar bad person, especially where I know T9 has done its thing again... But for some reason I find the comparison between Kerbals and corn kernels hilarious XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-22T23:28:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222424869\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-